c:T5a8,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Huntington Beach have sea level rise risks?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, coastal flooding from sea level rise is a growing threat. Low-lying areas near the beach and Huntington Harbour are increasingly vulnerable to tidal flooding and storm surge."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What neighborhoods face coastal flooding?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Seacliff, The Strand, and areas near Huntington Harbour are most vulnerable. Storm events combined with high tides can flood coastal roads and beachfront properties."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Huntington Harbour flood?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Huntington Harbour can experience flooding during strong storm events when drainage systems are overwhelmed and combine with high tides."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are beach erosion concerns real in Huntington Beach?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, chronic beach erosion affects the coastline. Winter storms with high waves erode beaches, exposing properties to wave damage and increasing flood risks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Bolsa Chica area flood?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Bolsa Chica area, including the ecological reserve, experiences tidal flooding during extreme events. Adjacent residential areas can be affected by overflow."}}]}2:[["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 md:py-24","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6","children":[["$","$L8",null,{"href":"/","className":"hover:text-white","children":"Home"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-2","children":"/"}],["$","$L8",null,{"href":"/locations","className":"hover:text-white","children":"Locations"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-2","children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Huntington